				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The grayscale bit simply masks the lower four bits of each palette entry, so colors $00-0F get drawn as color $00, colors $10-1F become $10, and so on.  Games typically use this bit for flashing effects, such as the effect when you pick up a Triforce piece at the end of each level in Legend of Zelda.</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />"Last version was better," says Floyd. "More bugs. Bugs make game fun."</div>
